headline.main: VICHY PUTS STRESS ON INTERNAL ISSUES; But No Surprise Is Caused as Cabinet Communique Fails to Note 'Collaboration'

lead_paragraph: VICHY, France, Oct. 18 -- Once again, at a time when. French-German relations absorb general interest, the communique issued after a Saturday Cabinet Council is devoted entirely to internal questions. That fact causes no surprise, however, since it is realized that conversations upon "collaboration" may be prolonged before any concrete decisions are made public.
abstract: Cabinet communique devoted to internal questions
